You are working on the Hublio project.

Before making any change, read **AGENTS.md**.

AGENTS.md is the single source of truth for architecture, coding standards, package layout, and database design.

## Goals

* Preserve the architecture.
* Generate production-ready Go code.
* Keep the codebase simple and maintainable.

## Tech Stack

* Go
* PostgreSQL
* Redis
* Next.js
* TypeScript
* TanStack Query
* TailwindCSS
* shadcn/ui

## Architecture

Follow the Architecture Freeze.

Do not introduce

* Microservices
* CQRS
* Event Sourcing
* BPMN
* Workflow Engine
* Rule Engine

Use the existing Runtime Model:

Intent

↓

Execution

↓

Execution Step

↓

Connector Runtime

↓

External System

## Package Rules

Always use the existing package layout.

```
internal/

    identity/

    integration/

    orchestration/

    transformation/

    events/

    platform/
```

Do not create new architectural layers.

## Dependency Rules

Dependencies must always point inward.

```
Interfaces

↓

Application

↓

Domain

↑

Infrastructure
```

The Domain must never import Infrastructure.

## Connectors

Provider-specific code belongs only in

```
internal/integration/connectors/
```

Do not leak provider DTOs into the Domain.

## Database

Follow the database schema.

Do not rename tables or columns.

Do not redesign relationships.

## Coding

Prefer

* Constructor Injection
* Small Interfaces
* Explicit Code
* Early Returns
* Table-driven Tests

Avoid

* Global Variables
* Reflection
* Hidden Dependencies
* Utility Packages
* Over-engineering

## Before Completing Any Task

Verify

* Architecture respected
* Package boundaries respected
* Business rules remain in Domain
* Tests added where appropriate
* Code compiles
* No duplicated logic

When in doubt, follow AGENTS.md.
